    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@wilsoncusack \r\n\r\nforge does not resolve direct import paths pointing inside the src dir\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nimport {Foo, Bar} from \"src/Foo.sol\";\r\n```\r\n\r\nshould rather be \r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nimport {Foo, Bar} from \"./Foo.sol\";\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, the solidity docs say that these imports\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nimport \"./math/math.sol\";\r\nimport \"contracts/tokens/token.sol\";\r\n```\r\n\r\nin `contracts/contract.sol` are resolved to\r\n\r\n```\r\ncontracts/tokens/token.sol\r\ncontracts/math/math.sol\r\n```\r\n\r\nso we should consider this a bug and also basically add the equivalent of this \"src/=src/\" remapping when resolving direct imports.\r\n\r\n",
