    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "After looking into this, this is another case where solc's VFS does not play nice with ethers-solc\r\n\r\nfor \"src/Foo.sol\", solc expects a `Source` in the `CompilerInput` that also has the path \"src/Fool.sol\", not the absolute path like ethers-solc currently provides.\r\n\r\nThe easiest way to support these paths is by providing an additional remapping \"\\<source dir name>=/absolute path to /src/\".\r\nwhich we could manually add when we configure the `Project` and its remappings in foundry\r\nwdyt @gakonst ?",
